.TH scroll 3
.SH NAME
\*Lscroll\*O \- Scrolls the window
.SH SYNOPSIS
.PP
.sS
\*L#include <curses.h>\*O

\*Lint scroll(\*Vwin\*L)
    WINDOW \(**\*Vwin\*L;\*O
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.iX "scroll subroutine"
The window is scrolled up one line.
This involves moving the lines in the window data structure.
.PP
You would not normally use this routine as the terminal
scrolls automatically if \*Lscrollok\*O is enabled.
A typical case where \*Lscroll\*O
might be used is with a screen editor.
.SH RETURN VALUES
.PP
The \*Lscroll\*O function returns OK on success and ERR on error.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.PP
\*Lscrollok\*O(3)
.EQ
